      "variant": "main",
      "html": "\n\n<div>\n<h3><span>Reinforcing the Substitution Method</span></h3><span>\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-e9fb3d15-7fff-f24f-27ba-1b05164a01db\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Solve the system by substitution:&nbsp;</p>\n<div data-cnxml-to-html-ver=\"2.8.0\" data-type=\"page\" id=\"page_b9f8475e-9490-4f24-995f-2923b1ed9644\">\n<section data-depth=\"1\" id=\"fs-id1167834233994\">\n<div data-type=\"example\" id=\"fs-id1167835415482\">\n<div>\n<div data-type=\"exercise\" id=\"fs-id1167832057897\">\n<div data-type=\"problem\" id=\"fs-id1167832057899\">\n<div>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167832057901\"><math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>{</mo>\n<mtable>\n<mtr>\n<mtd columnalign=\"left\">\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mtd>\n</mtr>\n<mtr>\n<mtd columnalign=\"left\">\n<mn>6</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>8</mn>\n</mtd>\n</mtr>\n</mtable>\n</mrow>\n<mo></mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>{</mo>\n<mtable>\n<mtr>\n<mtd columnalign=\"left\">\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mtd>\n</mtr>\n<mtr>\n<mtd columnalign=\"left\">\n<mn>6</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>8</mn>\n</mtd>\n</mtr>\n</mtable>\n</mrow>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</span>\n\n<div data-cnxml-to-html-ver=\"2.8.0\" data-type=\"page\" id=\"page_b9f8475e-9490-4f24-995f-2923b1ed9644\">\n<section data-depth=\"1\" id=\"fs-id1167834233994\">\n<div data-type=\"example\" id=\"fs-id1167835415482\">\n<div>\n<div data-type=\"exercise\" id=\"fs-id1167832057897\">\n<div data-type=\"solution\" id=\"fs-id1167835595520\">\n<div>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167835595522\">We need to solve one equation for one variable. We will solve the first equation for <span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-e9fb3d15-7fff-f24f-27ba-1b05164a01db\"><span>\\( y \\)</span></span></span>.</p>\n<div>\n<table data-label id=\"fs-id1167826998205\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><br></td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-alt=\".\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167835254444\"><img alt=\".\" data-media-type=\"image/jpeg\" id=\"41\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/b26c9fe0fc53db396540476ec5818fe7504dfbc7\"></span> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">Solve the first equation for <em data-effect=\"italics\">y</em>.<span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span>Substitute <math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math> for <em data-effect=\"italics\">y</em> in the second equation.</td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-alt=\".\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167835379481\"><img alt=\".\" data-media-type=\"image/jpeg\" id=\"42\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/19c9733d575875f9552ff96a8b8e0c67788e6f76\"></span> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">Replace the <em data-effect=\"italics\">y</em> with <math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-alt=\".\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167831239705\"><img alt=\".\" data-media-type=\"image/jpeg\" id=\"43\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/51b25ba97507303a9a192945d793bb9fddaf5b53\"></span> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">Solve the equation for <em data-effect=\"italics\">x</em>.</td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-alt=\".\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167834432973\"><img alt=\".\" data-media-type=\"image/jpeg\" id=\"44\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/83e66e705128e6a9e6294aa015ba82cef57fd2e1\"></span> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">Substitute <math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math> into <math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math> to find <em data-effect=\"italics\">y</em>.</td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-alt=\".\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167835609313\"><img alt=\".\" data-media-type=\"image/jpeg\" id=\"45\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/bf156f08ea8b1a4ba9298fd36065699ae6ad0d69\"></span> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><br></td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">The ordered pair is <math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">Check the ordered pair in both equations.<span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span><span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span><span data-alt=\".\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167835175410\"><img alt=\".\" data-media-type=\"image/jpeg\" id=\"46\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/38376a4623c4aedf597ab9a582ea0701da31c9a1\"></span></td>\n<td><br></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><br></td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">The solution is <math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div><br>\n<h4>Try It: Reinforcing the Substitution Method</h4>\n</span>\n</div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-69eeabcd-7fff-73e4-c2b7-5a427adf1ddf\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Solve the system by substitution: </p>\n<div data-cnxml-to-html-ver=\"2.8.0\" data-type=\"page\" id=\"page_b9f8475e-9490-4f24-995f-2923b1ed9644\">\n<section data-depth=\"1\" id=\"fs-id1167834233994\">\n<div data-type=\"note\" id=\"fs-id1167826782993\">\n<div>\n<div data-type=\"exercise\" id=\"fs-id1167826782996\">\n<div data-type=\"problem\" id=\"fs-id1167826782998\">\n<div>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167826783000\"><math display=\"inline\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>{</mo>\n<mtable>\n<mtr>\n<mtd columnalign=\"left\">\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>&minus;4</mn>\n</mtd>\n</mtr>\n<mtr>\n<mtd columnalign=\"left\">\n<mo>&minus;</mo>\n<mn>3</mn>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mi>y</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mtd>\n</mtr>\n</mtable>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</semantics>\n</math></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</span>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n<p>Write down your answer. Then select the&nbsp;<strong>Solution</strong>&nbsp;button to check your work.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n<span>Here is how to solve by substitution:<br></span><br><span>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<table>\n<colgroup>\n<col width=\"169\">\n<col width=\"551\">\n</colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Solve the first equation for \\( x \\) to isolate a variable.</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">\\(\\begin{array}{rcl}\\;\\;x\\;&ndash;\\;4y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;&ndash;4\\\\x\\;&ndash;\\;4y\\;{\\style{color:red}+}\\;{\\style{color:red}4}{\\style{color:red}y}\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;&ndash;4\\;{\\style{color:red}+}\\;{\\style{color:red}4}{\\style{color:red}y}\\\\x\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;&ndash;4\\;+\\;4y\\end{array}\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span><strong>Step 2:</strong></span></span> Replace the \\(x\\) in the second equation with the expression \\( -4 + 4y \\).</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">\\(\\begin{array}{rcl}&ndash;3x\\;+\\;4y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;0\\\\&ndash;3{\\style{color:red}(}{\\style{color:red}&ndash;}{\\style{color:red}4}\\;{\\style{color:red}+}\\;{\\style{color:red}4}{\\style{color:red}y}{\\style{color:red})}\\;+\\;4y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;0\\end{array}\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span><strong>Step 3:</strong></span></span> Solve the equation with just one variable.</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>\\(\\begin{array}{rcl}&ndash;3(&ndash;4\\;+\\;4y)\\;+\\;4y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;0\\\\12 - 12y\\;+\\;4y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;0\\\\&ndash;8y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;&ndash;12\\\\y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;\\;\\frac32\\end{array}\\)</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span><strong>Step 4:</strong></span></span> Use the first equation and replace \\(y\\) with 32.</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">\\(\\begin{array}{rcl}x\\;&ndash;\\;4y\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;&ndash;4\\\\x\\;&ndash;\\;4(\\frac32)\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;&ndash;4\\\\x\\;&ndash;\\;6\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;&ndash;4\\\\x\\;&amp;=&amp;\\;2\\end{array}\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span><strong>Step 5:</strong> </span></span>The ordered pair is \\((x, y)\\).</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span> &nbsp; &nbsp; \\((2,\\frac32)\\)</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Step 6:</strong></span> Substitute \\( x=6 \\), \\( y=1 \\) to check the solution in both equations.</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>\\(\\begin{array}{r}x\\;&ndash;\\;4y\\;=\\;&ndash;4\\\\\\;{\\style{color:red}(}{\\style{color:red}2}{\\style{color:red})}\\;&ndash;\\;4{\\style{color:red}(}\\frac{\\style{color:red}3}{\\style{color:red}2}{\\style{color:red})}\\stackrel{?}{=}&ndash;4\\\\\\;2\\;&ndash;\\;6\\stackrel{?}{=}&ndash;4\\\\&ndash;4\\;=\\;&ndash;4\\;{\\style{color:red}\u2714}\\end{array}\\)</span><br></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><br></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">\\(\\begin{array}{r}&ndash;3x\\;+\\;4y\\;=\\;0\\\\\\;-3{\\style{color:red}(}{\\style{color:red}2}{\\style{color:red})}\\;&ndash;\\;4{\\style{color:red}(}\\frac{\\style{color:red}3}{\\style{color:red}2}{\\style{color:red})}\\stackrel{?}{=}0\\\\\\;-6\\;+\\;6\\stackrel{?}{=}0\\\\0\\;=\\;0\\;{\\style{color:red}\u2714}\\end{array}\\)</p>\n\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</span><br><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f84c4c8f-7fff-42fb-8a81-43b63eddce9c\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">How did you do? Know that you learn more from wrong answers than from right answers! Wrong answers help us find flaws in our thinking. Take a minute to think about why you got the question wrong. Then you won&rsquo;t get this type of question wrong again!</p>\n</div>\n</span><br>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->"
    }
